Body:
How do I fix these errors in NodeMCU, which reports that multiple libraries were found for servo.h?

Multiple libraries were found for Servo.h"	 Used: C:\Users\username\AppData\Local\Arduino15\packages\esp8266\hardware\esp8266\2.4.1\libraries\Servo	 Not used: C:\Program Files (x86)\Arduino\libraries\Servo	exit status 1	'myservo' does not name a type
"
Possible duplicate of [Multiple libraries were found servo.h](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/49704566/multiple-libraries-were-found-servo-h)
The NodeMCU boards use theire own librarys to controll servos. You can't use the normal servo library with the NodeMCU.
